comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T03:38:19.258Z",maintainer-agent,"Duplicate-check 2026-07-21: all-status search (graph/slack/centrality/betweenness/articulation/critical-path) found no existing item for these three primitives; this is the granular deliverable under umbrella pm-7ob5 (which stays open for structural-holes, temporal what-if, and the million-item eval matrix). Not a duplicate of pm-7ob5 (the 7-bullet umbrella) nor of the shipped communities/redundancy/dominators analytics."
  "2026-07-21T03:38:19.888Z",maintainer-agent,"Verification evidence 2026-07-21: full sandboxed coverage passed 324 files / 6038 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (statements 40605/40605, branches 28585/28585, functions 8240/8240, lines 39504/39504). pnpm lint passed: ESLint 0 warnings, jscpd 0 clones, static-quality (100% docstrings incl. exported+member, complexity), package-boundary, token-budget (14 surfaces). Contracts snapshot regenerated. Manual dogfood in a temp workspace built a diamond+shortcut ordering DAG and confirmed pm graph slack (makespan 4, shortcut task slack 1, critical path A->B->C->D), pm graph centrality (betweenness ranking with directed fan-in/out), and pm graph articulation (correctly reports zero cuts on the biconnected diamond). New unit specs: scheduling.spec.ts (7), centrality.spec.ts (12); integration in run.spec.ts (+3). All three subcommands verified across CLI human + --json + --summary output."
  "2026-07-21T03:53:54.410Z",maintainer-agent,"Pre-push Greptile review 207a768a-6eae-4a2f-a76b-81c1931e54d9 (confidence 4/5, safe to merge): accepted both P2 findings. (1) runGraphSlack silently ignored --kind while the cache key still recorded it — fixed by rejecting --kind for slack in assertGraphFlagScope (fail-fast usage error, consistent with --rebuild/--save-baseline scoping) rather than a silent drop; added a rejection regression. (2) GraphScheduleOptions.signal docstring claimed two abort checks but the simplified implementation checks once at entry — corrected the docstring. Greptile confirmed the three algorithms are implemented correctly and well-tested."
  "2026-07-21T04:31:01.268Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #625 bot-review round 1 dispositioned (CodeRabbit/Greptile/Gemini/Sourcery). FIXED: (1) fan-in/fan-out semantic direction (Greptile P1 + Gemini high) — directed degrees now orient by declared precedence via a new shared orientOrderingEdge helper (traversal.ts) and are scoped to ordering/dependency kinds, matching orderingPredecessors/orderingSuccessors; also de-dups scheduling's inline orientation. (2) Schedule cycle-downstream exclusion (Greptile P1/P2) — docstrings corrected: tasks transitively gated by a cycle are omitted (undefined earliest start), regression added. (3) Cut-structure signal docstring (CodeRabbit) — 'once per depth-first step'. Tests added (Sourcery): inverse-kind matching, mixed ordering/non-ordering schedule, empty-workspace envelopes for the 3 new subcommands, non-summary articulation truncation. DECLINED with rationale (replied+downvoted inline): abort-signal propagation (analyzeRelationshipExecution has no signal param; O(V) backward pass), localeCompare determinism (matches graph-SDK id-ordering convention; ASCII ids), slack cost metadata (whole-graph exact analysis, no bounded-traversal cost), fused adjacency/degree pass (different structures, negligible cost). Every inline comment + review body up/down-voted and answered. Full suite exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-21T04:42:30.255Z",maintainer-agent,"Merged delivery: PR #625 squash-merged to main as 341408db. pm graph slack/centrality/articulation shipped with precedence-oriented fan-in/out, cycle-downstream schedule docs, and cut-structure signal docs after two review rounds. All required checks green (Greptile Review pass; all Gates/CodeQL/Trivy/TruffleHog/Semgrep/Windows/coverage pass); CodeRabbit withdrew its localeCompare finding and accepted the docstring fix; every bot comment/review up/down-voted + answered; all 12 review threads resolved. Full suite exact 100/100/100/100."
